  "text": "The results are shown in Fig. 4 .5. Figure 4 .5(a) shows a side view of the datasetX . Each data point x ∈X is colored proportionally to its out-of-sample extension distortion rate µ(x) (see step 3 in Algorithm 5.) Classification ofX to either normal or abnormal classes is shown in Fig. 4.5(b) . The normal class N ⊂ is darkly colored and the abnormal classN is brightly colored. The classification was done according to Definition 2.2. Thus, x ∈X is classified as normal if its distortion rate satisfies µ(x) ≤ µ. Otherwise, it is classified as abnormal. Lastly, a two dimensional view of the out-of-sample extension of the normal class, namely h [CITATION_1] s (x), x ∈ N , is shown in Fig. 4.5(c) . Each embedded data point is colored in the same color as its nearest neighbor from the embedding of X by h ",
